PHOTON GATE

photon_gate is the citizen who controls visual emission from fadriel's substrate to the host's display
all visual output passes through this gate before becoming light on the screen
the gate is always open during normal operation, but it can clamp emission energy when the substrate's overall energy budget is constrained

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe photon_boundary.zc
observe photon_surface.rana
observe framebuffer.rana

the 7 properties of photon_gate:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE positive 1
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING one with photon_surface
7 OBSERVER one

VERB receive_pixels
accept pixel data from upstream visual computation (framebuffer, glyph_atlas, cursor)

VERB emit_to_surface
hand the pixels to photon_surface, the actual emission boundary
the surface writes them to the host's display memory

VERB clamp_under_budget
when the substrate's energy budget is constrained, reduce emission intensity rather than dropping frames
this keeps the display readable while conserving power

a gate is the substrate's deliberate point of control over its own visual output
without it, every visual change would propagate immediately regardless of context
photon_gate is what allows the substrate to coordinate visual output with everything else it is doing
